var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en","zh"],"separator":"[\\s\\u200b\\u3000\\-\u3001\u3002\uff0c\uff0e\uff1f\uff01\uff1b]+","pipeline":["stemmer"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"en/index.html","title":"AedtToolbox Help Documentation","text":"<p>Welcome to AedtToolbox \u2014 a floating toolbar for Ansys Electronics Desktop (AEDT) that provides rapid script execution and tool integration.</p>"},{"location":"en/index.html#quick-navigation","title":"Quick Navigation","text":"<ul> <li> <p>AedtToolbox Overview   Startup, menu operations, Python environment configuration  View Docs</p> </li> <li> <p>Custom Menu Items   Add custom menu entries, scripts and external programs  View Docs</p> </li> <li> <p>HFSS 3D Layout Utilities   Stackup import, backdrill, port ordering and more  View Docs</p> </li> <li> <p>Toolkits   Transmission line modeling, PyAEDT panel installer  View Docs</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoBackdrill.html","title":"AutoBackdrill","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoBackdrill.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Via \u2192 AutoBackdrill</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoBackdrill.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>Automatically sets up via backdrill based on net names and stub length. Supports AEDT 2023 R1 and later. Automatically determines the backdrill direction.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoBackdrill.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>Ensure the 3D Layout project is selected, then right-click Toolbox and select Via \u2192 AutoBackdrill. The AutoBackdrill settings dialog will appear.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <ul> <li>Net Match (Regex) \u2014 Use a regular expression to match nets for backdrill. Default <code>.*</code> matches all nets.</li> <li>Backdrill Stub \u2014 Backdrill stub length accuracy; default is 8 mil.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoBackdrill.html#net-match-regex","title":"Net Match (Regex)","text":"<ul> <li>Use <code>.*</code> to match any number of characters. For example, <code>DQ.*</code> matches all nets starting with <code>DQ</code>.</li> <li>Regex syntax reference: https://www.runoob.com/regexp/regexp-syntax.html</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoBackdrill.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<ul> <li>Bus notation is also supported. For example, <code>DQ[15:0]</code> matches nets <code>DQ0</code> through <code>DQ15</code>.   (Note: this bus notation is not standard regex \u2014 it is an extension supported by this tool.)</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoXNet.html","title":"AutoXNet","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoXNet.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Net \u2192 AutoXNet</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoXNet.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>When a signal trace passes through a capacitor and one side of the net is unnamed (numeric or random name), this script automatically names the unnamed side based on the already-named side. New net names are suffixed with <code>_C</code>, <code>_R</code>, or <code>_L</code> depending on component type (currently defaults to capacitors only).</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoXNet.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>Ensure the 3D Layout project is selected, then right-click Toolbox and select Net \u2192 AutoXNet. The script runs automatically in the active AEDT session, detecting capacitor nets and naming any unnamed ones.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/AutoXNet.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<ul> <li>Power/GND nets defined in 3D Layout are automatically skipped.</li> <li>Capacitors must be assigned to the Capacitors category in the Component list.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html","title":"ExportToHfssWithNets","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Export \u2192 ExportToHfssWithNets</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>After exporting a 3D model from 3D Layout to HFSS, this script groups objects by Net, making it easier to browse and configure them.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>Ensure the 3D Layout project is selected and fully configured (stackup, ports, cutout, etc.), with an HFSS Setup defined (ideally only one). Then right-click Toolbox and select Export \u2192 ExportToHfssWithNets.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#result","title":"Result","text":"<p>After the script completes, the result looks like:</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#overlapping-stackup-support","title":"Overlapping Stackup Support","text":"<p>For 2.5D/3DIC packages using Overlapping stackup in 3D Layout, ExportToHfssWithNets supports the export. However, if two or more metal layers share the same height, Net recognition may have issues.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#interposer-export-example","title":"Interposer Export Example:","text":"<ol> <li>Overlapping stackup with all metal layers at different heights </li> <li>Before exporting, the Design Mode must be General Mode, otherwise the script will fail </li> <li>Export result </li> </ol>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ExportToHfssWithNets.html#note","title":"Note","text":"<p>3D Layout using the HFSS solver achieves the same accuracy as HFSS 3D, but is faster and easier to set up. In most cases, exporting to HFSS 3D is not recommended.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html","title":"ImportCSVStackup","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Stackup \u2192 ImportCSVStackup</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>Quickly import a stackup from a CSV file provided by the PCB manufacturer. Convert the manufacturer's xlsx file into the provided CSV template format. Column order is flexible; unrecognized columns are ignored.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>Fill in the stackup information using the provided CSV template. Then right-click Toolbox, select Stackup \u2192 ImportCSVStackup, and choose the completed CSV file to import.</p> <p>Two templates are provided in the <code>ImportCSVStackup.py</code> directory: - <code>CsvStackupTemp_full.csv</code> - <code>CsvStackupTemp_simple.csv</code></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#template-format","title":"Template Format","text":"Layer Type Thickness(mil) Cond DK DF Roughness UNNAMED_000 dielectric 0 3.7 0.15 0.5um TOP signal 1.9 3.7 0.15 0.5um UNNAMED_002 dielectric 2.65 3.5 0.004 0.5um PWR signal 1.3 3.5 0.004 0.5um UNNAMED_004 dielectric 50 3.5 0.004 0.5um LYR_1 signal 1.2 3.5 0.004 0.5um UNNAMED_006 dielectric 8 3.5 0.004 0.5um LYR_2 signal 1.2 3.5 0.004 0.5um UNNAMED_008 dielectric 8 3.5 0.004 0.5um GND signal 1.3 3.5 0.004 0.5um UNNAMED_010 dielectric 2.65 3.5 0.004 0.5um BOTTOM signal 1.9 3.7 0.15 0.5um UNNAMED_012 dielectric 0 3.7 0.15 0.5um <p>Notes: 1. <code>Layer</code>, <code>Type</code>, and <code>Thickness</code> are required; rows without them are ignored. 2. If <code>Cond</code>, <code>DK</code>, or <code>DF</code> are missing or empty, defaults of Copper and FR4_epoxy are used. 3. <code>Thickness</code> can specify units in parentheses, or include units in the value itself. 4. <code>Roughness</code> is optional. Groiss format: <code>0.5um</code>; Huray format: <code>0.5um;2.9</code></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#optional-columns","title":"Optional Columns","text":"<ul> <li>Thickness \u2014 Layer thickness with unit, or use a global unit in the header (e.g. <code>Thickness(mil)</code> or <code>Thickness(mm)</code>)</li> <li>Material \u2014 Material name from the system library (e.g. <code>Copper</code>); when specified, <code>Cond</code>/<code>DK</code>/<code>DF</code> are ignored</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<ul> <li>The number of metal layers in the CSV must match the PCB; otherwise the import will fail.</li> <li>The number of dielectric layers does not need to match \u2014 if they differ, the CSV dielectric layers will override those in the PCB.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/ImportCSVStackup.html#usage-example","title":"Usage Example","text":"<ol> <li>Excel stackup file from the PCB manufacturer </li> <li>Export existing stackup template using ExportCSVStackup </li> <li>Import the modified CSV using ImportCSVStackup </li> <li>Log output </li> </ol>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/KeepHDIViaPad.html","title":"KeepHDIViaPad","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/KeepHDIViaPad.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Via \u2192 KeepHDIViaPad</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/KeepHDIViaPad.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>3D Layout omits intermediate pads on HDI stacked vias by default, even though those pads physically exist. The KeepHDIViaPad script detects HDI through-holes and adds equal-size circular shapes on each layer to simulate the actual pads.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/KeepHDIViaPad.html#result","title":"Result","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html","title":"RenameEdgePort","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Port \u2192 RenameEdgePort</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>Renames manually added ports in 3D Layout for easier identification.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#naming-rules","title":"Naming Rules","text":"<ul> <li>If the port is on a Pin: named as <code>refdes.pin.Net</code> \u2014 e.g. <code>U1.A2.DQ0</code></li> <li>If the port is not on a Pin: named using the net name</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>After adding ports manually, keep the 3D Layout window in focus and run Port \u2192 RenameEdgePort. Ports are automatically updated.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#result","title":"Result","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#before","title":"Before","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#after","title":"After","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/RenameEdgePort.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<p>Renaming coupled wave ports (one wave port with 2 or more terminals) is not currently supported.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/deleteInvalidRLC.html","title":"DeleteInvalidRLC","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/deleteInvalidRLC.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Component \u2192 DissolveInvalidRLC (&lt;2 pins) Component \u2192 deleteInvalidComponents (&lt;2 pins)</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/deleteInvalidRLC.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>Removes RLC components that have only one valid net connection. After performing a Cutout or deleting nets in a layout, some RLC components may have their nets removed and become invalid. This command clears those invalid RLC components.</p> <ul> <li>DissolveInvalidRLC (&lt;2 pins) \u2014 Only dissolves the RLC component; does not remove pads</li> <li>deleteInvalidComponents (&lt;2 pins) \u2014 Deletes all components with fewer than 2 pins (RLC and others) including their pads</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/deleteInvalidRLC.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>Ensure the 3D Layout project is selected, then right-click Toolbox and select Component \u2192 deleteInvalidRLC. The script runs automatically in the active AEDT session, detects net status of RLC components, and removes invalid ones.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html","title":"orderPorts","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":"<p>Port \u2192 orderPorts</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<p>Sorts 3D Layout ports by Net using the following rules: 1. Component (refdes) 2. Bus index (numeric suffix on net name) 3. Differential pair P/N, +/\u2212, P/M</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#how-to-use","title":"How to Use","text":"<p>Keep the 3D Layout window in focus and run Port \u2192 orderPorts.</p>"},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#result","title":"Result","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#before","title":"Before","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#after","title":"After","text":""},{"location":"en/HFSS3DLayout/orderPorts.html#s-parameter-output-example","title":"S-parameter output example","text":"<pre><code># GHz S MA R 50.000000\n! Terminal data exported\n! Port[1] = XS23.AE19.MCTR2_CNIP1CH2FP_GTX_T0_P\n! Port[2] = XS23.AD19.MCTR2_CNIP1CH2FP_GTX_T0_N\n! Port[3] = XS23.AE21.MCTR2_CNIP1CH2FP_GTX_T1_P\n! Port[4] = XS23.AD21.MCTR2_CNIP1CH2FP_GTX_T1_N\n! Port[5] = XS23.AE23.MCTR2_CNIP1CH2FP_GTX_T2_P\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html","title":"Welcome to Aedt Toolbox","text":""},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<p>AedtToolbox provides a convenient way to quickly run scripts or external programs within AEDT. It combines a floating icon with a customizable menu for efficient operation. Users can rapidly customize menu contents via XML files to manage scripts, and any changes are immediately reflected in the right-click menu, ensuring a personalized experience.</p> <p>Overall effect: </p> <p>When a menu item is clicked, Toolbox sends the script to the most recently opened AEDT window and executes it. Since Toolbox is version-agnostic, the same script can run across different AEDT versions.</p> <p>Toolbox supports execution of external programs and scripts including: EXE, Python, and IronPython. Currently only Windows is supported.</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#getting-started","title":"Getting Started","text":"<p>Launch Toolbox by running <code>AedtToolbox.exe</code>. After startup, Toolbox displays as a floating window on top of all other windows by default.</p> <p></p> <p>Two ways to open the right-click menu: 1. Right-click on the floating window  2. Right-click the notification tray icon </p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#keep-on-top","title":"Keep on Top","text":"<p>Function: Controls whether the Toolbox window stays above all other windows.</p> <ul> <li>Enabled \u2014 Toolbox window stays on top of all applications at all times</li> <li>Disabled \u2014 Toolbox window can be covered by other windows</li> </ul> <p>Characteristics: - Takes effect immediately without restarting - Session-scoped only; resets to default on restart (controlled by <code>toolbox.cfg</code>)</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#keep-log-window","title":"Keep Log Window","text":"<p>Function: Controls whether the command window stays open after Python/IronPython script execution.</p> <ul> <li>Enabled \u2014 The command prompt (cmd) stays open after execution for viewing output and debugging   <code>Execution: cmd /K python entry.py ... (/K keeps window open)</code></li> <li>Disabled \u2014 The command window closes immediately after execution   <code>Execution: python entry.py ... (closes when done)</code></li> </ul> <p>Characteristics: - State is persisted to <code>toolbox.cfg</code> and survives restarts - Does not affect EXE-type external programs - Applies to Python and IronPython scripts only</p> <p>Use Cases: - Development/Debugging \u2014 Enable to see script output and errors - Production \u2014 Disable for a clean execution experience</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#python-environment-configuration","title":"Python Environment Configuration","text":"<p>Toolbox uses automatic detection to find Python and IronPython in priority order.</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#python-detection-order-highest-to-lowest-priority","title":"Python Detection Order (highest to lowest priority)","text":"<ol> <li>Custom PyAEDT venv \u2014 <code>%APPDATA%\\.pyaedt_env\\3_10\\Scripts</code> (user-defined virtual environment)</li> <li>System PATH \u2014 Searches PATH for <code>python.exe</code> (user-installed Python)</li> <li>AEDT bundled CPython \u2014 <code>ANSYSEM_ROOTxxx\\common\\commonfiles\\CPython\\3_10\\winx64\\Release\\python</code></li> <li>IronPython \u2014 <code>ANSYSEM_ROOTxxx\\common\\IronPython</code> (always added to PATH for IronPython scripts)</li> </ol>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#installing-the-pyaedt-library","title":"Installing the pyaedt Library","text":"<p>For Python scripts, pyaedt is required. Install with:</p> <pre><code>pip install pyaedt\n</code></pre> <p>Or use the provided Toolkit: Toolkits \u2192 InstallPyaedtPannel</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/index.html#recommended-configuration","title":"Recommended Configuration","text":"<p>Option A: Use PyAEDT Virtual Environment (Recommended) - Create a venv at <code>%APPDATA%\\.pyaedt_env\\3_10\\Scripts</code> - Install pyaedt and dependencies - Highest priority, unaffected by system Python changes</p> <p>Option B: Use System Python - Install Python 3.10+ and add to system PATH - Run: <code>pip install pyaedt</code> - Simple setup, suitable for single-user environments</p> <p>Option C: Use AEDT Bundled Python - No setup required if AEDT &gt;= 2023.2 is installed - Lower priority; used as fallback</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html","title":"Custom Menus and Scripts","text":""},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<p>Users can add menus and scripts to build a customized Toolbox suited to their company's needs. Use the methods below to add or remove menu items and scripts.</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#menu-storage-location","title":"Menu Storage Location","text":"<p>Toolbox menu files are stored in the <code>Menu/</code> directory in XML format.</p> <p>Directory structure:</p> <pre><code>Toolbox installation directory/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 AedtToolbox.exe\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 Menu/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Default.xml              (base template, applies to all designs)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 CircuitDesign.xml        (Circuit design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 HFSS.xml                 (HFSS design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 HFSS-IE.xml              (HFSS-IE design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 HFSSIE.xml               (HFSS IE design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Maxwell2D.xml            (Maxwell 2D design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Maxwell3D.xml            (Maxwell 3D design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 HFSS3DLayoutDesign.xml   (3D Layout design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Icepak.xml               (Icepak design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Q2DExtractor.xml         (Q2D Extractor design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 Q3DExtractor.xml         (Q3D Extractor design specific)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 TwinBuilder.xml          (TwinBuilder design specific)\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 EMIT.xml                 (EMIT design specific)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 ...\n</code></pre> <p>Menu file types:</p> File Purpose Priority Default.xml Common menu for all design types Base {DesignType}.xml Design-specific menu (e.g. HFSS.xml, Maxwell3D.xml) Higher"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#menu-loading-logic","title":"Menu Loading Logic","text":"<p>Toolbox uses a smart menu merge mechanism to dynamically load and merge menus based on the currently active AEDT design type.</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#loading-flow","title":"Loading Flow","text":"<pre><code>User right-clicks Toolbox\n    \u2193\ncontextMenuStrip1_Opening event fires\n    \u2193\nDetermine menu path\n    \u251c\u2500 Detect active AEDT window\n    \u251c\u2500 Query active design type\n    \u251c\u2500 Generate menu filename (e.g. Menu/HFSS.xml)\n    \u2514\u2500 Check if file exists\n    \u2193\nLoad and merge menus\n    \u251c\u2500 Load {DesignType}.xml (ordering authority)\n    \u251c\u2500 Load Menu/Default.xml (content supplement)\n    \u2514\u2500 Merge via MergeXmlNodes()\n    \u2193\nMergeXmlNodes merge rules\n    \u251c\u2500 {DesignType}.xml order is the reference\n    \u251c\u2500 Items from Default.xml fill missing positions\n    \u251c\u2500 Relative order from Default.xml is preserved\n    \u2514\u2500 Recursively merges sub-menus\n    \u2193\ngenerateMenu() builds UI\n    \u2514\u2500 Creates ToolStripMenuItems and binds click events\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#key-features","title":"Key Features","text":"<p>1. Design type detection - Automatically detects the active AEDT design type - Falls back to Default.xml if no design-specific file exists</p> <p>2. Merge rules - Order authority \u2014 {DesignType}.xml determines display order - Content priority \u2014 {DesignType}.xml definitions take precedence - Auto supplement \u2014 Default.xml items are inserted at missing positions - Relative position preserved \u2014 Supplemented items keep their relative order from Default.xml</p> <p>Example:</p> <pre><code>Default.xml order:  Help \u2192 SyncServer \u2192 About \u2192 Exit\nHFSS.xml order:     Tool \u2192 Toolkits \u2192 Exit\n\nMerged result:      Tool \u2192 Toolkits \u2192 Help \u2192 SyncServer \u2192 About \u2192 Exit\n                    \u2191       \u2191         \u2191        \u2191           \u2191       \u2191\n                  HFSS    HFSS    Default   Default      Default Default\n</code></pre> <p>3. Live reload After editing any XML file in the Menu/ directory, Toolbox automatically reloads on the next menu open \u2014 no restart required.</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#menu-format","title":"Menu Format","text":"<pre><code>&lt;Menu&gt;\n    &lt;SubMenu Name=\"test\"&gt;\n        &lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"showProjectName_python\"\n                 ExecuteType=\"Python\" Path=\"$UserLib/Template/showProjectName.py\"\n                 Arguments=\"\" PythonPath=\"\" LogWindow=\"True\"/&gt;\n        &lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"showProjectName_Ironpython\"\n                 ExecuteType=\"IronPython\" Path=\"$UserLib/Template/showProjectName.py\"\n                 Arguments=\"\" EntryFunc=\"main\" PythonPath=\"\"/&gt;\n    &lt;/SubMenu&gt;\n&lt;/Menu&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#parameter-reference","title":"Parameter Reference","text":"Parameter Description Name Display name of the menu item Type <code>MenuItem</code> (default), <code>Separator</code> ExecuteType <code>Python</code>, <code>IronPython</code>, <code>EXE</code> (<code>Command</code> is reserved for internal use) Path Script or executable path. Prefix with <code>$</code> for relative paths (e.g. <code>$UserLib/\u2026</code>) Arguments Arguments passed to the script, space-separated PythonPath Override Python executable path (optional) EntryFunc Entry function name (default: <code>main</code>) LogWindow <code>True</code> (default) keeps log window open; <code>False</code> hides it"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<ul> <li>Spaces and Chinese characters in file paths may cause execution errors \u2014 avoid them  </li> <li>Use <code>\\\\</code> or <code>/</code> for path separators in XML  </li> <li>XML syntax must be valid; syntax errors prevent menu loading  </li> <li>XML comments are known to cause loading errors \u2014 do not use comments in XML files </li> <li>After saving edited XML, Toolbox reloads automatically</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#adding-an-exe-file","title":"Adding an EXE File","text":"<pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"Notepad\" ExecuteType=\"EXE\"\n         Path=\"Notepad.exe\" Arguments=\"\"/&gt;\n</code></pre> Parameter Description Name Menu display name ExecuteType <code>EXE</code> Path Executable path. Can also specify a document (e.g. <code>xxx.docx</code>) if the OS has a default handler Arguments Arguments, space-separated LogWindow Whether to show log window"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#adding-a-python-script","title":"Adding a Python Script","text":"<pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"QuitAedt\" ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n         Path=\"$UserLib/Desktop/Close.py\" EntryFunc=\"ForceQuitAedt\"\n         Arguments=\"\" PythonPath=\"\"/&gt;\n</code></pre> Parameter Description Name Menu display name ExecuteType <code>Python</code> Path Script path; use <code>$</code> prefix for relative paths Arguments Optional; arguments passed to the script PythonPath Optional; override Python executable path EntryFunc Optional; entry function (default: <code>main</code>) LogWindow Show log window on execution"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/AddItem.html#adding-an-ironpython-script","title":"Adding an IronPython Script","text":"<pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"QuitAedt\" ExecuteType=\"IronPython\"\n         Path=\"$UserLib/Desktop/Close.py\" EntryFunc=\"ForceQuitAedt\"\n         Arguments=\"\" PythonPath=\"\"/&gt;\n</code></pre> Parameter Description Name Menu display name ExecuteType <code>IronPython</code> Path Script path; use <code>$</code> prefix for relative paths Arguments Optional; arguments passed to the script PythonPath Optional; override IronPython executable path EntryFunc Optional; entry function (default: <code>main</code>) LogWindow Show log window on execution"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/Close.html","title":"close","text":""},{"location":"en/ToolBox/Close.html#menu-location","title":"Menu Location","text":""},{"location":"en/ToolBox/Close.html#description","title":"Description","text":"<ul> <li>Close \u2192 QuitAedt: Force quit AEDT</li> <li>Close \u2192 CloseProjectAndSave: Close current project and save</li> <li>Close \u2192 CloseProjectNotSave: Close current project without saving</li> <li>Close \u2192 CloseAllProjectAndSave: Close all projects and save</li> <li>Close \u2192 CloseAllProjectNotSave: Close all projects without saving</li> <li>Close \u2192 ReloadProject: Reload the current project</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/UDM_UDP.html","title":"Adding UDM / UDP Scripts","text":"<p>UDM and UDP enable more complex model construction and can be used in HFSS, Icepak, Maxwell 3D, and Q3D. The tool supports adding UDM and UDP scripts to the menu as follows:</p> <pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"UDPTest\" ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n         Path=\"xxxx/geodesic_sphere.py\" EntryFunc=\"$UDP\" LogWindow=\"False\"/&gt;\n&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"UDMTest\" ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n         Path=\"xxxx/OnDieSpiralInductor.py\" EntryFunc=\"$UDM\" LogWindow=\"False\"/&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/UDM_UDP.html#parameter-description","title":"Parameter Description","text":"<p>When <code>EntryFunc</code> is set to <code>$UDM</code>, the tool treats the script as a UDM script and sends it to the corresponding AEDT window to execute the UDM command. When <code>EntryFunc</code> is set to <code>$UDP</code>, the tool treats the script as a UDP script and sends it to the corresponding AEDT window to execute the UDP command. For release builds, set <code>LogWindow=\"False\"</code> to prevent the log window from appearing. For other parameters, refer to the Write your Script documentation.</p> <p>UDM and UDP scripts are written following the standard AEDT script guide \u2014 save as <code>.py</code> files and place them anywhere. Relative paths with <code>$</code> prefix can be used for files within the tool directory. The execution behavior is identical to clicking the menu item in AEDT software \u2014 a settings dialog will appear.</p> <ol> <li> <p>Select the corresponding UDP or UDM script from the right-click menu </p> </li> <li> <p>The UDP/UDM settings dialog appears </p> </li> </ol> <p>Note: The tool automatically adds a <code>UDMScript</code>/<code>UDPScript</code> entry under UDM/UDP as an entry point. If removed, it will be regenerated. (If the user lacks write permissions to the <code>sysLib</code> directory, manually add <code>UDMScript</code>/<code>UDPScript</code> to the <code>UserLib</code> directory.)</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/WriteScript.html","title":"Writing Custom Scripts","text":""},{"location":"en/ToolBox/WriteScript.html#python-script-development","title":"Python Script Development","text":"<p>Python scripts can be developed normally. Wrap the functionality into a function and specify it as the entry function in the XML menu configuration. The default entry function is <code>main()</code> \u2014 using <code>main()</code> as the entry point is recommended.</p> <p>The example below defines multiple functions in one Python file. Different functions can be specified as entry points in the XML to achieve different actions. Alternatively, the same function can handle different behaviors via <code>Arguments</code>.</p> <pre><code>import sys, os\n\nModule = sys.modules['__main__']\nif hasattr(Module, \"oDesktop\"):\n    oDesktop = getattr(Module, \"oDesktop\")\nelse:\n    raise Exception(\"oDesktop initialization error.\")\n\n\ndef closeAndSave():\n    oProject = oDesktop.GetActiveProject()\n    oProject.Save()\n    oProject.Close()\n\ndef closeNotSave():\n    oProject = oDesktop.GetActiveProject()\n    oProject.Close()  # Unsaved changes will be lost.\n\ndef closeAllProjectWithSave():\n    projects = oDesktop.GetProjects()\n    for oProject in projects:\n        oProject.Save()\n        oProject.Close()\n\ndef closeAllProjectWithoutSave():\n    projects = oDesktop.GetProjects()\n    for oProject in projects:\n        oProject.Close()\n\ndef ForceQuitAedt():\n    oDesktop.QuitApplication()\n\ndef Reload():\n    oProject = oDesktop.GetActiveProject()\n    aedtPath = os.path.join(oProject.GetPath(), oProject.GetName() + \".aedt\")\n    oProject.Close()\n    print(\"Reload aedt: %s\" % aedtPath)\n    oDesktop.OpenProject(aedtPath)\n</code></pre> <p>XML menu configuration:</p> <pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Name=\"Close\"&gt;\n    &lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"QuitAedt\" ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n             Path=\"$UserLib/Desktop/Close.py\" EntryFunc=\"ForceQuitAedt\"/&gt;\n    &lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"CloseProjectAndSave\" ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n             Path=\"$UserLib/Desktop/Close.py\" EntryFunc=\"closeAndSave\"/&gt;\n    &lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"CloseProjectNotSave\" ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n             Path=\"$UserLib/Desktop/Close.py\" EntryFunc=\"closeNotSave\"/&gt;\n&lt;/SubMenu&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/update.html","title":"Updates","text":""},{"location":"en/ToolBox/update.html#download-aedttoolbox-from-github","title":"Download AedtToolbox from GitHub","text":"<p>https://github.com/YongshengGuo/AedtToolbox/releases/latest</p> <p>https://gitcode.com/GuoYongsheng/AedtToolbox</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/update.html#download-pyaedt-offline-package","title":"Download pyaedt Offline Package","text":"<p>The tool requires pyaedt to be installed. If network access is restricted and pip installation is not possible, download the offline package for your Python version from: https://github.com/ansys/pyaedt</p>"},{"location":"en/ToolBox/update.html#contact","title":"Contact","text":"<p>yongsheng.guo@synopsys.com</p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html","title":"Q2D Transmission Line Modeling &amp; Optimization (TransmissionLineToolkit)","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<p>TransmissionLineToolkit is a parametric PCB transmission line modeling and simulation tool based on Ansys Q2D Extractor. It provides a GUI supporting multiple trace types for building Q2D models, estimating characteristic impedance, and running full-wave simulations. The tool runs via IronPython inside AEDT and creates Q2D designs directly.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#requirements","title":"Requirements","text":"<ul> <li>Runtime: Ansys Electronics Desktop (AEDT) 2022 R1 or later</li> <li>Script engine: IronPython (AEDT built-in)</li> <li>Design type: Q2D Extractor</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#tool-location","title":"Tool Location","text":"<pre><code>Toolbox installation directory/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 UserLib/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Toolkits/\n\u2502       \u2514\u2500\u2500 q2d_tlineToolkit/\n\u2502           \u251c\u2500\u2500 TransmissionLineToolkit.py   (main entry script)\n\u2502           \u251c\u2500\u2500 Q2D\u8d70\u7ebf\u5efa\u6a21\u4e0e\u4f18\u5316\u8bbe\u8ba1.pdf    (user guide)\n\u2502           \u2514\u2500\u2500 TLine/\n\u2502               \u251c\u2500\u2500 MainForm.py             (GUI main form)\n\u2502               \u251c\u2500\u2500 anstDebug.py            (logging module)\n\u2502               \u2514\u2500\u2500 Images/                (UI image assets)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 ...\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#calling-from-toolbox-menu","title":"Calling from Toolbox Menu","text":"<p>Add the following to your menu XML:</p> <pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\"\n         Name=\"TransmissionLine Toolkit\"\n         ExecuteType=\"IronPython\"\n         Path=\"$UserLib/Toolkits/q2d_tlineToolkit/TransmissionLineToolkit.py\"\n         EntryFunc=\"main\"\n         Arguments=\"\" /&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#supported-trace-types","title":"Supported Trace Types","text":"Trace Type Description Typical Use Microstrip - Single Ended Single-ended microstrip Surface layer single-ended signals Microstrip - Differential Differential microstrip Surface layer diff pairs (USB, HDMI) Stripline - Single Ended Single-ended stripline Inner layer single-ended signals Stripline - Differential Differential stripline Inner layer diff pairs (PCIe, DDR) Stripline - Broadside Coupled Broadside coupled stripline High-density differential routing Grounded Coplanar Waveguide GCPW High-frequency RF/microwave signals"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#gui-layout","title":"GUI Layout","text":"<pre><code>\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502  [ANSYS Logo]  [Model Export]  [GUI]   \u2502  \u2190 Top panel\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\n\u2502  [Design type selection dropdown]      \u2502\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\n\u2502                 \u2502  Design Parameters    \u2502\n\u2502  Cross-section  \u2502  \u251c\u2500 Trace dimensions  \u2502\n\u2502  diagram        \u2502  \u251c\u2500 Units             \u2502\n\u2502  (live update)  \u2502  \u2514\u2500 Material props    \u2502\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\n\u2502  [Sim Params Tab] [Etch Tab] [Rough Tab]\u2502\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\n\u2502  Zo = xx \u03a9 (estimated)  [Simulate]     \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#units","title":"Units","text":"<p>Supported unit systems (global effect):</p> Unit Description mil Mils (recommended, common in PCB) inches Inches microns Micrometers millimeters Millimeters"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#trace-parameter-reference","title":"Trace Parameter Reference","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#geometry-parameters","title":"Geometry Parameters","text":"Parameter Applicable Structures Description Trace Width All Trace width Trace Thickness All Copper trace thickness Trace Spacing Multi-trace Spacing between traces Number of Traces Single/Differential Number of trace conductors Differential Spacing Differential Intra-pair spacing Plane Thickness All Reference ground plane copper thickness Top Dielectric Stripline / GCPW Dielectric thickness above trace Bottom Dielectric All Dielectric thickness below trace Solder Mask Thickness Microstrip Solder mask thickness"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#dielectric-properties-per-layer","title":"Dielectric Properties (per layer)","text":"Parameter Default Description Er 4.0 Relative permittivity Tand 0.02 Loss tangent Reference frequency 1 GHz Frequency at which properties are specified Frequency unit GHz Hz / kHz / MHz / GHz selectable"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#advanced-settings-tabs","title":"Advanced Settings Tabs","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#tab-1-simulation-parameters","title":"Tab 1: Simulation Parameters","text":"Parameter Default Description Solution Frequency 10 GHz Q2D solve frequency Frequency Sweep None Sweep type Start / Stop / Step \u2014 Sweep range and step <p>Sweep types: None (single point), Discrete, Interpolating (recommended)</p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#tab-2-etching","title":"Tab 2: Etching","text":"<p>Models the trapezoidal cross-section from real PCB manufacturing:</p> Setting Description No Etch No etching (rectangular cross-section) Over Etch (Top) Top narrower than bottom Under Etch Top wider than bottom Etch Factor Etch percentage (slider control)"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#tab-3-surface-roughness","title":"Tab 3: Surface Roughness","text":"Model Parameters Description No Roughness \u2014 Ideal smooth surface Hammerstad Rq (Top/Sides/Bottom) Classic empirical roughness model Hall-Huray Roughness + ratio (Top/Sides/Bottom) High-accuracy physics-based model <p>Roughness units: um / mil / nm</p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#simulation-workflow","title":"Simulation Workflow","text":"<pre><code>1. Select trace type from dropdown\n2. Enter geometry parameters\n3. Set dielectric material properties (Er, Tand, frequency)\n4. (Optional) Configure etching parameters\n5. (Optional) Configure surface roughness model\n6. Set solution frequency and sweep settings\n7. Select model export format\n8. Click [Simulate]\n   \u2192 Q2D design created in AEDT, simulation runs automatically\n   \u2192 View Zo, differential impedance and other results\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#characteristic-impedance-estimation","title":"Characteristic Impedance Estimation","text":"<p>Click Calculate (when visible) to instantly estimate Zo using IPC empirical formulas \u2014 no simulation needed.</p> <p>Note: IPC formulas are approximations; accuracy is lower than Q2D full-wave simulation.</p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#model-export-formats","title":"Model Export Formats","text":"Format Description Use Case Tabular W-element Frequency-dependent RLGC matrix Circuit simulation (HSPICE, ADS) Lumped Element Lumped RLC model Quick estimation, lower accuracy"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#typical-design-parameters","title":"Typical Design Parameters","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#50-microstrip-fr4","title":"50\u03a9 Microstrip (FR4)","text":"Parameter Typical Value Trace width ~90 mil (1oz copper, 4 mil dielectric) Copper thickness 1.4 mil (1oz) / 2.8 mil (2oz) Dielectric thickness 4\u20138 mil Er (FR4) 3.9\u20134.5 @ 1 GHz Tand (FR4) 0.015\u20130.025"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#100-differential-stripline","title":"100\u03a9 Differential Stripline","text":"Parameter Typical Value Trace width ~4 mil Intra-pair spacing ~5 mil Dielectric (above/below) 4\u20138 mil each"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"Issue Cause Solution Tool won't start Not running inside AEDT Must be called via AEDT IronPython Images not loading TLine/Images/ missing Check that the Images directory is complete Simulation error Insufficient Q2D license Check AEDT license status Abnormal Zo value Parameters out of valid range Check inputs against IPC specifications Empty exported model Simulation not complete Wait for simulation to finish before exporting"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/TransmissionLineToolkit.html#logging","title":"Logging","text":"<ul> <li>Default level: INFO</li> <li>Log location: AEDT temp directory (<code>oDesktop.GetTempDirectory()</code>)</li> <li>Log filename: <code>TLine_*.log</code></li> </ul> <p>For verbose debug logging, change in <code>TransmissionLineToolkit.py</code>:</p> <pre><code>oLog = anstDebug.anstDebug('TLine', logging.DEBUG, oDesktop)\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html","title":"PyAEDT Panel Installer (addPyaedtPanels)","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<p>addPyaedtPanels is a standardized PyAEDT panel installer with a GUI that simplifies PyAEDT configuration and integration on Windows. It supports installing PyAEDT from multiple sources and automatically integrates it into the AEDT design environment.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#requirements","title":"Requirements","text":"<ul> <li>OS: Windows</li> <li>Python: 3.10 or higher</li> <li>AEDT: 2023.2 or higher</li> <li>Network: Supports both online and offline (wheel file) installation</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#tool-location","title":"Tool Location","text":"<pre><code>Toolbox installation directory/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 UserLib/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 Toolkits/\n\u2502       \u2514\u2500\u2500 addPyaedtPanels/\n\u2502           \u251c\u2500\u2500 install_pyaedt_gui.py       (main GUI application)\n\u2502           \u251c\u2500\u2500 refactor_utils.py           (shared utility functions)\n\u2502           \u2514\u2500\u2500 *.pdf                       (user guide)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 ...\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#key-functions","title":"Key Functions","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#1-virtual-environment-management-create_venv","title":"1. Virtual Environment Management (<code>create_venv</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Creates a dedicated Python 3.10 virtual environment</li> <li>Location: <code>%APPDATA%\\.pyaedt_env\\3_10\\</code> (Windows)</li> <li>Detects existing environments to avoid re-creation</li> <li>Isolated dependency management \u2014 does not affect system Python</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#2-pyaedt-installation","title":"2. PyAEDT Installation","text":""},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#online-installation-install_pyaedt_online","title":"Online Installation (<code>install_pyaedt_online</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Installs the latest version with automatic dependency resolution</li> <li>Requires network access</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#offline-installation-install_pyaedt_from_wheel","title":"Offline Installation (<code>install_pyaedt_from_wheel</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>No network required; fast installation</li> <li>Requires pre-downloaded <code>.whl</code> or <code>.zip</code> file</li> <li>Ideal for corporate networks and multi-machine deployment</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#3-aedt-panel-registration-add_pyaedt_to_aedt","title":"3. AEDT Panel Registration (<code>add_pyaedt_to_aedt</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Registers PyAEDT as AEDT design panels</li> <li>Calls PyAEDT's official installer script</li> <li>Auto-creates <code>PersonalLib</code> directory if missing</li> </ul>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#workflow","title":"Workflow","text":"<pre><code>Launch install_pyaedt_gui.py\n    \u2193\nDetect AEDT environment\n    \u251c\u2500 Running inside AEDT \u2192 relaunch with AEDT CPython 3.10\n    \u2514\u2500 Standalone \u2192 continue with system Python 3.10+\n    \u2193\nGUI opens\n    \u251c\u2500 Select installation method (online / offline)\n    \u251c\u2500 Manage virtual environment\n    \u251c\u2500 Monitor installation progress\n    \u2514\u2500 Result feedback\n    \u2193\nCreate virtual environment\n    \u2514\u2500 At %APPDATA%\\.pyaedt_env\\3_10\\\n    \u2193\nInstall PyAEDT\n    \u251c\u2500 Online: pip install pyaedt[all]\n    \u2514\u2500 Offline: pip install --find-links=&lt;path&gt;\n    \u2193\nRegister AEDT panels\n    \u2514\u2500 ansys.aedt.core.extensions.installer.pyaedt_installer\n    \u2193\nComplete \u2014 restart AEDT to apply changes\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#python-environment-priority","title":"Python Environment Priority","text":"<p>The installed venv integrates with Toolbox's Python detection hierarchy:</p> Priority Source Path 1 (highest) Custom user venv <code>%APPDATA%\\.pyaedt_env\\3_10\\Scripts\\python.exe</code> 2 System PATH <code>python.exe</code> in PATH 3 AEDT bundled <code>ANSYSEM_ROOT\\...\\CPython\\3_10\\...\\python.exe</code> 4 (lowest) IronPython <code>ANSYSEM_ROOT\\common\\IronPython</code>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#aedt-root-detection","title":"AEDT Root Detection","text":"<p>The tool auto-scans environment variables for AEDT installations:</p> <pre><code># Supported variable formats (case-insensitive):\nAnsysEM_ROOT241    # AEDT 2024.1\nANSYSEM_ROOT232    # AEDT 2023.2\n</code></pre> <p>Multiple versions are sorted descending \u2014 the newest version is used.</p>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#gui-launch-methods","title":"GUI Launch Methods","text":"<p>Method 1: Via Toolbox menu \u2192 select \"PyAEDT Panel Installer\"</p> <p>Method 2: Command line:</p> <pre><code>python install_pyaedt_gui.py\n</code></pre> <p>Method 3: AEDT IronPython console:</p> <pre><code>exec(open(r\"C:\\...\\addPyaedtPanels\\install_pyaedt_gui.py\").read())\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#toolbox-menu-integration","title":"Toolbox Menu Integration","text":"<pre><code>&lt;SubMenu Type=\"MenuItem\" Name=\"Install PyAEDT Panel\"\n         ExecuteType=\"Python\"\n         Path=\"$UserLib/Toolkits/addPyaedtPanels/install_pyaedt_gui.py\"\n         EntryFunc=\"main\" /&gt;\n</code></pre>"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#troubleshooting","title":"Troubleshooting","text":"Issue Cause Solution \"AEDT Python not found\" AEDT version too old Upgrade AEDT to 2023.2+ Permission denied No write access to venv path Modify %APPDATA% permissions or change install path Installation timeout Unstable network Use offline wheel installation or retry PersonalLib not found AEDT hasn't created default dir Handled automatically \u2014 no action needed"},{"location":"en/Toolkits/addPyaedtPannel.html#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<ol> <li>Do not modify <code>install_pyaedt_gui.py</code> \u2014 it is generated from a standard template</li> <li>Restart AEDT after installing to load the new panels</li> <li>Permissions: Write access to <code>%APPDATA%</code> is required</li> <li>Uninstall: Delete <code>%APPDATA%\\.pyaedt_env\\</code> to fully remove the virtual environment</li> </ol>"}]}